# SimCountry OS — Cursor Rules

You are working on SimCountry OS, a digital nation sandbox built with Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Supabase, and Solana wallet adapter.

## Behavior Rules

- Always use TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.
- Use App Router patterns: server components by default, `'use client'` only when required.
- Keep components under 200 lines. Extract sub-components when they grow.
- Import from exact file paths — no barrel exports.
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly. Do not create new CSS files unless adding to `globals.css`.
- Use the `.glass` class for all panel/card backgrounds.
- Always handle loading and error states for async data.

## UI Conventions

- Background: `#0a0a0f` (`bg-[#0a0a0f]`)
- Panels: `.glass` class (defined in globals.css)
- Accent: `text-blue-400` / `bg-blue-500`
- Reward accent: `text-amber-400`
- Labels: `text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500`
- Status dots: `w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full` with color by status

## File Conventions

- Pages: `app/route/page.tsx` — default export, PascalCase function name
- Components: `components/ComponentName.tsx` — named export
- Types: defined in `lib/supabase.ts` or inline for UI-only types
- Hooks (v1+): `hooks/useHookName.ts`

## Data Conventions

- Supabase client: import from `@/lib/supabase`
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` on the client
- Citizen slot status union: `'npc' | 'claimable' | 'claimed'`
- Mission status union: `'active' | 'completed' | 'expired' | 'locked'`
- District types: `arts | government | commerce | knowledge | trade | faith`

## Do Not

- Do not install new packages without checking for an existing solution first
- Do not create mock API routes when static data in the page file will suffice for v0
- Do not add animations with framer-motion — use Tailwind transitions only
- Do not add `console.log` to production code
- Do not use `!important` in CSS
